==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[pastor]]''', ''shepherd'', + adjective suffix '''[[-alis]]'''

===Adjective===
(Pas"tor*al) [L. ''pastoralis'': cf. F. ''pastoral''. See [[Pastor]].]
#Of or pertaining to shepherds; hence, relating to rural life and scenes; as, a pastoral life.
